body:
@perryao That is indeed the only commit related to this issue. 

I used the fork for some other fixes and updates, guess I had better put the PR in a separate branch, but didn't think this PR would take this long, seeing how broken the current plugin executor code is.

There is no way I can change the branch this PR references in my fork right? (I tried)

@bolkedebruin I sorted out the forks master branch, which now only contains the commit which fixes the two issues.

As mentioned before, I would like to add unit tests, but seeing how the issues are tied to physical plugin files and import cycles when loading airflow, I have no idea how to contain this within a unit test. I am on the airflow slack if you wish to discuss adding tests.

To be clear, the current unit tests are sufficient to test the changes when no executor plugins are used and when they are used, the current implementation is confirmed to be broken in a bad way, so even if we don't figure out the unit tests immediately it would still be a big improvement to include this PR in the next release.
